## 4. The "Hand Feel" Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-Hard (47.5° ESN scale), dense, and highly tensioned.
    - Feedback: Firm but springy. You can clearly feel the tension of the rubber firing the ball back.
    - Hold vs. Release: Strong bias toward release. It grabs the ball briefly but shoots it out rapidly.
    - Dwell Time: Short to Medium. It depends heavily on how deeply you compress the sponge, but generally, it wants to eject the ball quickly.

- Sound/Click
    - Loud and metallic. It produces a very satisfying, sharp "click" sound on power loops, a hallmark of its ESN tensor generation.

